messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Full path
- /api/orders/{id}/deliver

All HTTP methods acceptable?
- false

HEAD
- false

POST
- false

OPTIONS
- false

TRACE
- false

GET
- false

PUT
- true

DELETE
- false

PATCH
- false

Explanation
- server.js mounts the router at the prefix /api/orders: app.use('/api/orders', orderRoutes).
- routes/orderRoutes.js registers the route router.route('/:id/deliver').put(protect, admin, updateOrderToDelivered); so the route path after the prefix is /:id/deliver and the registered HTTP method is PUT. Combining prefix + route yields /api/orders/{id}/deliver.
- Although the controller comment in controllers/orderController.js mistakenly documents the route as GET /api/orders/:id/deliver, the actual router registers a PUT handler, so GET is not accepted for this path.
- No .all() or wildcard registration is used, so "all methods" is false.
- Express only provides automatic HEAD handling for routes that have a GET handler; since this path only has a PUT handler, HEAD is not automatically accepted.
- OPTIONS, TRACE, POST, DELETE, PATCH are not defined for this path in the code, so they are not acceptable.
